functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

msg.content: What are the five categories of the 65th Annual Grammy Awards and who is the winner for each category?
What are the five categories of the 65th Annual Grammy Awards and who is the winner for each category?

The 65th Annual Grammy Awards were held on February 5, 2023. The main awards were presented in 86 categories, under 5 main categories. Here are the winners from each category:

- General Field:
Harry's House, performed by Harry Styles (Album of the Year)
Justified, performed by Doja Cat (Record of the Year)
About Damn Time, performed by Lizzo (Song of the Year)
Samara Joy (Best New Artist)

- Pop Field:
Music for a Sushi Restaurant, performed by Harry Styles (Best Pop Solo Performance)
Don't Shut Me Down, performed by ABBA (Best Pop Duo/Group Performance)
Harry's House, performed by Harry Styles (Best Pop Vocal Album)
Special, performed by Lizzo (Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album)

- Dance/Electronic Music Field:
Break My Soul, performed by Beyoncé (Best Dance/Electronic Recording)
Déjà vu, performed by Beyoncé (Best Dance/Electronic Album)

- Rock Field:
Broken Horses, performed by Brandi Carlile (Best Rock Performance)
Black Summer, performed by Metallica (Best Metal Performance)
Patient Number 9, performed by Ozzy Osbourne featuring Jeff Beck (Best Rock Song)
Music of the Spheres, performed by Coldplay (Best Rock Album)
The Patient, performed by Ozzy Osbourne featuring Jeff Beck (Best Hard Rock Performance)

- R&B Field:
Hrs & Hrs, performed by Muni Long (Best R&B Performance)
Cuff It, performed by Beyoncé (Best R&B Song)
Good Morning Gorgeous, performed by Mary J. Blige (Best R&B Album)
